75
00:04:03,200 --> 00:04:04,120
Go to the Chengnan Sub-Bureau

76
00:04:04,120 --> 00:04:05,450
and get him the dossier.

77
00:04:11,680 --> 00:04:13,830
[Beijiang Detention Center]

78
00:04:27,010 --> 00:04:28,060
Did you see that?

79
00:04:28,650 --> 00:04:30,850
The judicial police are carrying guns.

80
00:04:32,180 --> 00:04:33,840
Someone is getting executed.

81
00:04:37,510 --> 00:04:38,190
Everyone here has committed

82
00:04:38,190 --> 00:04:39,780
a murder.

83
00:04:40,620 --> 00:04:42,050
A life for a life.

84
00:04:43,350 --> 00:04:44,650
Nothing to cry over.

85
00:04:46,170 --> 00:04:47,170
I don't believe

86
00:04:47,510 --> 00:04:48,640
you won't be scared

87
00:04:48,810 --> 00:04:49,940
when it's your turn.

88
00:04:51,500 --> 00:04:52,840
They can't execute me.

89
00:05:02,460 --> 00:05:03,860
As long as he's out there.

90
00:05:10,690 --> 00:05:12,750
What do you think

91
00:05:13,090 --> 00:05:16,450
[Chu Yingzi's Crime Scene Identification]

92
00:05:13,130 --> 00:05:14,720
a person would become

93
00:05:15,190 --> 00:05:16,650
after six years in prison?

94
00:05:16,950 --> 00:05:17,960
Do you intend to complete

95
00:05:17,960 --> 00:05:19,180
Bureau Chief Zhang's task,

96
00:05:19,180 --> 00:05:21,910
or do you just want to meet a prisoner on death row?

97
00:05:23,710 --> 00:05:24,930
Drop that thought.

98
00:05:25,310 --> 00:05:26,150
It's no use.

99
00:05:30,310 --> 00:05:31,190
Are you saying

100
00:05:31,190 --> 00:05:32,570
she has no accomplice?

101
00:05:33,500 --> 00:05:35,390
She has an accomplice for sure.

102
00:05:37,400 --> 00:05:39,200
I've already read the case file.

103
00:05:39,460 --> 00:05:41,350
There may be no footprints or fingerprints

104
00:05:41,350 --> 00:05:42,610
of a third person

105
00:05:42,610 --> 00:05:44,800
found at the two crime scenes.

106
00:05:44,800 --> 00:05:47,460
But judging by the dismemberment of the bodies,

107
00:05:48,159 --> 00:05:49,540
it's not something

108
00:05:49,540 --> 00:05:50,680
a woman can accomplish easily.

109
00:05:50,680 --> 00:05:52,480
Chu Yingzi wants to live.

110
00:05:52,900 --> 00:05:54,250
So she must prove

111
00:05:54,250 --> 00:05:55,840
the existence of this accomplice.

112
00:05:55,840 --> 00:05:57,100
Yet, she can't describe

113
00:05:57,100 --> 00:05:58,570
his actual appearance.

114
00:05:58,570 --> 00:06:00,130
If we arrest him,

115
00:06:00,670 --> 00:06:01,090
she'll be counting the days

116
00:06:01,090 --> 00:06:02,620
to the day of her execution.

117
00:06:02,640 --> 00:06:03,740
So it means

118
00:06:04,030 --> 00:06:04,490
she came up

119
00:06:04,490 --> 00:06:06,000
with these faces.

120
00:06:06,760 --> 00:06:07,470
No wonder

121
00:06:08,060 --> 00:06:08,650
the previous forensic artists couldn't

122
00:06:08,650 --> 00:06:09,910
do the composite drawing.

123
00:06:09,910 --> 00:06:11,040
Forensic artists are

124
00:06:11,040 --> 00:06:13,190
her tools to prolong her life.

125
00:06:14,320 --> 00:06:15,080
So

126
00:06:15,500 --> 00:06:17,030
you think I'm her next tool?

127
00:06:19,650 --> 00:06:20,370
She's precisely using

128
00:06:20,370 --> 00:06:22,260
the forensic artists' pencils

129
00:06:22,260 --> 00:06:22,890
to create

130
00:06:22,890 --> 00:06:24,750
a person that'll never be caught.

131
00:06:29,730 --> 00:06:34,310
[Beijiang Police Sub-Bureau, Interpol Team]

132
00:06:40,360 --> 00:06:41,030
Du.

133
00:06:42,800 --> 00:06:43,970
Shen left

134
00:06:43,970 --> 00:06:45,480
without finishing the news

135
00:06:45,480 --> 00:06:46,610
on the noticeboard.

136
00:06:46,659 --> 00:06:48,720
What's so urgent that he had to leave?

137
00:07:00,390 --> 00:07:02,790
[Beijiang Detention Center]

138
00:07:15,850 --> 00:07:17,150
Do I need to wait for you?

139
00:07:17,150 --> 00:07:18,660
[Occupied]

140
00:07:17,280 --> 00:07:19,280
You have to pay more if I have to wait.

141
00:07:20,260 --> 00:07:21,980
[City Center]

142
00:07:26,600 --> 00:07:30,630
[Beijiang Detention Center]

143
00:07:39,030 --> 00:07:40,170
Great paintings

144
00:07:41,290 --> 00:07:42,820
often recorded situations

145
00:07:42,900 --> 00:07:45,040
beyond human belief.

146
00:07:45,460 --> 00:07:46,210
That's why

147
00:07:46,760 --> 00:07:48,150
most great painters have a strange whim

148
00:07:48,150 --> 00:07:49,150
of going to the prison

149
00:07:49,150 --> 00:07:50,750
to draw death row prisoners.

150
00:07:51,800 --> 00:07:52,810
[Because that's where]

151
00:07:52,810 --> 00:07:54,270
[these painters can draw]

152
00:07:54,280 --> 00:07:55,830
[a human's most extreme emotion]

153
00:07:55,830 --> 00:07:57,510
[at the face of their deaths.]

154
00:07:58,350 --> 00:07:59,570
We can imagine

155
00:08:00,580 --> 00:08:02,380
what expression a human can show

156
00:08:02,510 --> 00:08:03,730
as they face death.

157
00:08:03,600 --> 00:08:08,600
[Women's Prison]

158
00:08:06,750 --> 00:08:08,310
Hogarth entered the prison

159
00:08:09,730 --> 00:08:11,200
to draw this portrait

160
00:08:11,200 --> 00:08:12,800
of this female serial killer

161
00:08:12,880 --> 00:08:14,180
before her execution.

162
00:08:16,120 --> 00:08:17,750
Just like you,

163
00:08:17,960 --> 00:08:19,100
everyone back then couldn't understand

164
00:08:19,100 --> 00:08:20,820
why the prisoner wasn't crying

165
00:08:20,820 --> 00:08:21,790
from fear

166
00:08:22,210 --> 00:08:23,470
before the execution.

167
00:08:23,890 --> 00:08:25,270
Instead, she showed calmness

168
00:08:25,270 --> 00:08:27,130
and indifference towards death.

169
00:08:35,100 --> 00:08:36,559
If an artist always sticks

170
00:08:36,650 --> 00:08:37,789
to painting a field

171
00:08:37,789 --> 00:08:39,470
that he can understand,

172
00:08:39,720 --> 00:08:41,400
he's doomed to mediocrity.

173
00:08:43,120 --> 00:08:45,890
Our brush should record

174
00:08:46,730 --> 00:08:49,660
the world's ultimate and outstanding achievement.

175
00:08:49,670 --> 00:08:59,120
[Women's Prison]

176
00:09:02,060 --> 00:09:07,360
[Beijiang Detention Center]

177
00:09:15,210 --> 00:09:15,920
Stand up!

178
00:09:17,730 --> 00:09:18,610
Inmate 0024,

179
00:09:18,610 --> 00:09:19,830
someone's here to see you.

180
00:09:19,830 --> 00:09:21,560
Follow me to the visiting room.

181
00:09:22,310 --> 00:09:23,150
Why?

182
00:09:24,360 --> 00:09:25,490
Is it a man or a woman?

183
00:09:26,460 --> 00:09:27,180
A man.

184
00:10:44,500 --> 00:10:45,380
Chu Yingzi.

185
00:10:55,670 --> 00:10:57,310
You're good-looking.

186
00:11:01,260 --> 00:11:02,860
I've been here for six years.

187
00:11:03,570 --> 00:11:05,370
I haven't seen any handsome man.

188
00:11:07,680 --> 00:11:08,680
Today's worth it.

189
00:11:10,410 --> 00:11:11,130
Thank you.

190
00:11:12,470 --> 00:11:13,480
You look good too.

191
00:11:14,320 --> 00:11:16,540
Strictly speaking, you're beautiful.

192
00:11:19,610 --> 00:11:21,740
Your face is completely symmetrical.

193
00:11:21,830 --> 00:11:23,470
The proportion ratios of your face are

194
00:11:23,470 --> 00:11:24,440
also balanced.

195
00:11:25,320 --> 00:11:26,370
Your face can be

196
00:11:27,130 --> 00:11:27,920
the prototype

197
00:11:27,920 --> 00:11:29,440
of classical sculpture.

198
00:11:31,450 --> 00:11:32,330
Is that so?

199
00:11:37,120 --> 00:11:39,100
Since I was around 12 to 13,

200
00:11:40,270 --> 00:11:42,410
guys have praised my beauty.

201
00:11:43,720 --> 00:11:44,580
I believe that.

202
00:11:46,360 --> 00:11:47,330
But none of what they said were

203
00:11:47,330 --> 00:11:48,760
as good as yours.

204
00:11:53,630 --> 00:11:54,470
It's a pity

205
00:11:59,630 --> 00:12:02,290
that you never saw what I looked like in the past.

206
00:12:03,960 --> 00:12:05,810
[Beijiang Detention Center]

207
00:12:06,900 --> 00:12:07,900
Not necessarily.

208
00:12:52,550 --> 00:12:53,180
This must be

209
00:12:53,180 --> 00:12:56,310
what you looked like when you were around 12 to 13, right?

210
00:13:04,820 --> 00:13:05,360
Have you seen

211
00:13:05,360 --> 00:13:07,420
the pictures of me when I was younger?

212
00:13:08,930 --> 00:13:09,560
No.

213
00:13:11,750 --> 00:13:12,170
I just drew

214
00:13:12,170 --> 00:13:13,260
a younger you

215
00:13:13,590 --> 00:13:15,120
based on your current look.

216
00:13:16,910 --> 00:13:17,750
I see.

217
00:13:20,440 --> 00:13:22,570
You're here to do a composite drawing.

218
00:13:24,430 --> 00:13:26,960
After so many times, isn't it enough already?

219
00:13:32,410 --> 00:13:33,810
All right. I'll tell you.

220
00:13:35,350 --> 00:13:36,650
He looks like

221
00:13:36,860 --> 00:13:39,340
a hero in the novels who robs the rich to help the poor.

222
00:13:39,340 --> 00:13:42,030
He's medium-built.

223
00:13:42,240 --> 00:13:43,920
Big eyes, thick eyebrows,

224
00:13:42,780 --> 00:13:46,520
[Beijiang Detention Center]

225
00:13:44,920 --> 00:13:46,180
and a beard.

226
00:13:50,220 --> 00:13:51,680
Is this what he looks like?

227
00:13:52,860 --> 00:13:53,530
Yes.

228
00:13:53,530 --> 00:13:55,260
You already have the portrait.

229
00:13:57,520 --> 00:13:58,530
What about these?

230
00:13:59,370 --> 00:14:01,090
Five forensic artists sketched

231
00:14:01,090 --> 00:14:02,420
six composite drawings

232
00:14:02,440 --> 00:14:04,540
of the suspect based on your descriptions.

233
00:14:04,540 --> 00:14:07,390
But every composite drawing is different.

234
00:14:07,390 --> 00:14:08,820
That's because they didn't do a good job.

235
00:14:08,820 --> 00:14:09,790
It was you who lied.

236
00:14:09,790 --> 00:14:11,320
It's up to you to believe me.

237
00:14:11,550 --> 00:14:13,230
I never lied.

238
00:14:18,940 --> 00:14:19,910
Perhaps I've been here

239
00:14:19,910 --> 00:14:21,550
for too long.

240
00:14:24,030 --> 00:14:25,960
I've forgotten what he looks like.

241
00:14:27,640 --> 00:14:29,190
How did he force you?

242
00:14:36,370 --> 00:14:37,090
He forced

243
00:14:39,190 --> 00:14:40,490
me to kill.

244
00:14:41,540 --> 00:14:42,000
He said

245
00:14:42,000 --> 00:14:43,510
if I didn't obey him,

246
00:14:44,860 --> 00:14:46,200
he'd kill me.

247
00:14:50,190 --> 00:14:51,390
You don't believe me?

248
00:14:51,530 --> 00:14:52,750
The eyes don't lie.

249
00:14:53,050 --> 00:14:54,380
When you talk about him,

250
00:14:56,150 --> 00:14:57,210
your eyes look like

251
00:14:58,720 --> 00:14:59,720
they're looking

252
00:14:59,720 --> 00:15:01,150
at a distant lover.

253
00:15:09,010 --> 00:15:09,850
Is that so?

254
00:15:14,970 --> 00:15:15,730
Chu Yingzi,

255
00:15:16,990 --> 00:15:17,950
do you know

256
00:15:17,950 --> 00:15:20,350
why I sketched a drawing of the younger you?

257
00:15:21,440 --> 00:15:22,400
I want you to know

258
00:15:23,240 --> 00:15:23,790
that I can let you see

259
00:15:23,790 --> 00:15:25,010
your past

260
00:15:25,930 --> 00:15:27,740
and let you see him again.

261
00:15:32,950 --> 00:15:34,550
Even if it's just a portrait.

262
00:15:36,220 --> 00:15:38,350
As long as you don't give away his name,

263
00:15:38,610 --> 00:15:40,250
both of you may be safe.

264
00:15:42,690 --> 00:15:44,450
It seems to be a perfect plan.

265
00:15:46,850 --> 00:15:47,770
But

266
00:15:48,320 --> 00:15:49,450
both of you are standing

267
00:15:49,450 --> 00:15:51,250
at the end of the board of a seesaw

268
00:15:51,470 --> 00:15:53,100
with a cliff below.

269
00:15:53,940 --> 00:15:55,800
You can only maintain the balance

270
00:15:58,020 --> 00:15:59,610
if you never meet.

271
00:16:01,460 --> 00:16:03,060
I don't know

272
00:16:03,560 --> 00:16:05,580
if a quick fall

273
00:16:06,800 --> 00:16:09,600
or the eternal separation is more painful for you.

274
00:16:11,290 --> 00:16:12,420
You'll live in

275
00:16:15,360 --> 00:16:17,340
this suffering in the future.

276
00:16:23,220 --> 00:16:25,280
Among the forensic artists I've met,

277
00:16:28,680 --> 00:16:29,270
you're the first

278
00:16:29,270 --> 00:16:30,800
who understands how I feel.

279
00:16:36,990 --> 00:16:38,000
[At first,]

280
00:16:39,300 --> 00:16:41,300
[his face was the first thing I saw.]

281
00:16:44,640 --> 00:16:45,770
After that,

282
00:16:48,710 --> 00:16:50,350
I saw his eyes.

283
00:16:59,040 --> 00:16:59,880
You're lying.

284
00:16:59,880 --> 00:17:00,970
Let me finish.

285
00:17:03,200 --> 00:17:04,420
The last one,

286
00:17:08,200 --> 00:17:10,000
I wanted to see his lips clearly.

287
00:17:10,000 --> 00:17:11,800
You started lying from the eyes.

288
00:17:11,849 --> 00:17:12,730
When the light of the lighter is close

289
00:17:12,730 --> 00:17:13,990
to the face,

290
00:17:13,990 --> 00:17:15,339
the human eyes will look away

291
00:17:15,339 --> 00:17:15,970
involuntarily

292
00:17:15,970 --> 00:17:17,270
due to the light.

293
00:17:18,490 --> 00:17:20,349
It'll never be like what you said.

294
00:17:25,710 --> 00:17:26,849
